<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>MiMealMoney</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bootstrap/5.3.2/css/bootstrap.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bootstrap-icons/1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/app.css" />
    <script src="/js/ThemeInterop.js"></script>
    <HeadOutlet />
</head>
<body>
    <Routes />
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bootstrap/5.3.2/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <!-- Stripe.js + Payment Element interop — used only by live installs (real keys); harmless in demo mode. -->
    <script src="https://js.stripe.com/v3/"></script>
    <script src="/js/stripe-payment.js"></script>
    @* Root-relative (leading slash) is REQUIRED. As a document-relative path this
       resolved against the current route — on /auth/login it requested
       /auth/_framework/blazor.server.js and 404'd, so Blazor never connected on ANY
       nested page. The forms then degraded to plain HTML POSTs and were rejected by
       UseAntiforgery() with HTTP 400 — i.e. sign-in and registration were dead. *@
    <script src="/_framework/blazor.server.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
